data.chText: 令人高兴的；令人满意的
data.enText: that gives you pleasure or satisfaction
a pleasing design
The new building was pleasing to the eye .
She had a pleasingly direct manner.

data.chText: 以上各词均形容经历、活动或现实令人满足或满意。
data.enText: These words all describe an experience, activity or fact that gives you pleasure because it provides sth you need or want.
satisfying
that gives you pleasure because it provides sth you need or want

data.chText: 一种游戏玩得特别好是一桩惬意的事。
data.enText: It's satisfying to play a game really well.
rewarding

data.chText: 指（经历或活动）有益的、有意义的、值得做的：
data.enText: (of an experience or activity) that makes you happy because you think it is useful or important; worth doing

data.chText: 做护士可以是非常有意义的职业。
data.enText: Nursing can be a very rewarding career.
pleasing

data.chText: 尤指令看到、听到、想到的人高兴、满意：
data.enText: ( rather formal ) that gives you pleasure, especially to look at, hear or think about

data.chText: 这是一项简单但令人满意的设计。
data.enText: It was a simple but pleasing design.
gratifying

data.chText: 指令人高兴，尤其对自己所做的事感到满意：
data.enText: ( formal ) that gives you pleasure, especially because it makes you feel that you have done well

data.chText: 看到这么好的结果真令人欣慰。
data.enText: It is gratifying to see such good results.
fulfilling

data.chText: 指（经历或活动）使人感到有意义、欣慰、满足（因为自己的技能和才干得以发挥）：
data.enText: (of an experience or activity) that makes you happy, because it makes you feel your skills and talents are being used

data.chText: 我现在觉得这工作有意义多了。
data.enText: I'm finding the work much more fulfilling now.

data.chText: 几乎任何经历（重要的或短暂的）均可用satisfying。rewarding和fulfilling多指较长或较重要的活动有意义，如工作或职业。satisfying和fulfilling多指个人的满足或幸福；rewarding则多指做了重要的或对他人有益的事时得到的满足感。
data.enText: Almost any experience, important or very brief, can be satisfying . Rewarding and fulfilling are used more for longer, more serious activities, such as jobs or careers. Satisfying and fulfilling are more about your personal satisfaction or happiness; rewarding is more about your sense of doing sth important and being useful to others.
satisfying, rewarding or fulfilling?
very/highly/extremely satisfying/rewarding/pleasing/gratifying/fulfilling
a satisfying/rewarding/gratifying/fulfilling experience/feeling
(a) satisfying/rewarding/fulfilling job/career/work
to be pleasing/gratifying to the eye/ear/senses
to find sth satisfying/rewarding/pleasing/gratifying/fulfilling

word_means: (常用在as或what、 where等词后)想，选择，喜欢

means: (常用在as或what、 where等词后)想，选择，喜欢

tr: the act of one who pleases

value.def: Something that is pleasing gives you pleasure and satisfaction.

example.ex: This area of France has a pleasing climate in August...
example.tran: 法国的这一地区在8月份气候宜人。
这样的景色令人心旷神怡。

example.ex: It's pleasing to see some criminals have a conscience.
example.tran: 看到有些罪犯还有良知让人感到欣慰。

value.tran: 令人愉快的；使人满意的

example.ex: The interior design is pleasingly simple...
example.tran: 室内设计简约朴素，令人惬意。

example.ex: He sets the atmosphere and shapes the scenes pleasingly.
example.tran: 他把气氛和场面调动得轻松愉快。
